      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NOW YOU SEE ME (7) went forward and proved too strong when resuming last time out, scoring by 5 lengths over 1000m at Northam. Will be up on the speed from the low draw. Finds a more suitable contest and can get the chocolates. MAJESTUOSO PHOENIX (5) is a four-year-old gelding who is having his first run for the Darryn Pateman yard. Resumes after filling a minor placing at his latest outing four-and-a-half months ago at Nowra. Not seen at the trials but is in a nice race. Definite winning chance. CLOSE TALKER (4) is back from a break of three months. Raced below par at her only appearance last prep when ninth over 1200m at Belmont Park. Kyra Yuill goes well on this five-year-old and is back on top today. One of the main contenders. BERRY BERRY GOOD (3) returned from a spell four weeks ago when he was beaten 4.5 lengths into fifth over 940m at Rockingham. Fitter this time will prove harder to beat.",
